summary: An ordinance relating to the municipal primary and general elections of 1945; certifying to the Election Board of King County, Washington, as required by law, a list of offices to be filled at said general municipal election; and requiring the City Comptroller and ex-officio City Clerk to certify to said Election Board, as required by law, the names of all persons filing declarations of candidacy for nomination at such primary election, and declaring an emergency.
